            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#martaf">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><w><expan><abbr>Θ</abbr><ex>εοῖς</ex></expan></w> <w><supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Κ</abbr><ex>αταχθονίοις</ex></expan></supplied></w>
                    <lb n="2"/><persName type="attested"><name>Σωτ<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">ηρ</supplied><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></name></persName>
                    <lb n="3"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="line"/>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text based on photographs</note></app>
                    <app loc="line 2"><note>Kaibel, Korhonen: Σωτ[ῆρ? ---]</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#martaf">
                <p>To the subterranean deities, Sot---</p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="it" resp="#martaf">
                <p>Agli dèi inferi, Sot---</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The invocation to the subterranean deities is followed by the name of the deceased, probably <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σωτῆρ</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σώταιρος</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σώτειρα</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σωτηρία</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σωτηρίδας</foreign>, <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σωτηρίς</foreign> (attested in an inscription from Catania dated to the 3rd-5th cent. CE: IG 14.550 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001369">ISic001369</ref>), <foreign xml:lang="grc">Σωτήριχος</foreign> (attested in an inscription from Catania dated to the imperial age: CIL 10.7054 = <ref target="http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic000338">ISic000338</ref>): on the names, see LGPN 3A: 417-419.</p>
            </div>
